msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Read the partitioning information for your architecture <e>now</e> and create\n"
"the partitions you'll use to store Gentoo Linux on. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filesystems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Partitions alone aren't sufficient to store data (unless the partition for a\n"
"specific purpose, like raw access for databases). You need to apply some\n"
"structure to the partition so that Linux knows where files and directories are\n"
"stored, what permissions are set to the file, what security attributes are\n"
"applied, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:423
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is the task of the file system. A <e>file system</e> is a standard way of\n"
"storing and retrieving information from a partition. It dictates where the files\n"
"data is stored and how to get access to the file <e>metadata</e> (everything\n"
"about a file except the content, like name, creation date, owner, ...). \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:430
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Linux supports quite a lot file systems, but not all of them are functional\n"
"enough to store Linux files. For instance, the FAT-family (FAT12 for floppies,\n"
"FAT16 for small partitions and FAT32 for larger ones) has no concept of\n"
"permissions while the NTFS-family (all the dozen versions that Microsoft has\n"
"released thus far) is too complex (partially due to its closed-source nature)\n"
"and not fully supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:439
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We will describe the most known file systems that you can use to hold your Linux\n"
"Operating System together with some information on the tools associated with the\n"
"file system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:447
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extended 3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:451
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Extended 3 is the <e>journaled</e> version of Extended 2, the older (but proven)\n"
"file system which is the first real Linux file system ever developed for Linux\n"
"(before ext2, the Minix file system was used - but that was a long, long time\n"
"ago). Extended 3 is currently the most used file system as well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As a <e>journaled</e> file system, ext3 can make sure that the entire file\n"
"system is consistent at any time. In other words, if your system would ever\n"
"crash (for instance due to a power interruption), the file system would never\n"
"contain garbled data - if you were busy writing data to the disk, either the old\n"
"data is there, or the new data, but not a partial write.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:466
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can choose between no journaling (which basically means that the file system\n"
"should be seen a an Extended 2), metadata journaling (where only the metadata is\n"
"consistent across time) where you can choose between writeback (first metadata\n"
"write, then data) and ordered (first data write, then metadata) and full\n"
"journaling. The ordered metadata journaling is the default.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:474
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Extended 3 supports access control lists and is therefore a candidate file\n"
"system for more security enhanced Linux kernels who require ACLs to be available\n"
"for the file system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:480
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To write an ext3 file system on a device, use the <c>mke2fs</c> tool with the\n"
"<c>-j</c> option (for <e>journaling</e>):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "Writing an ext3 file system on /dev/hda3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:485
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mke2fs -j /dev/hda3</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:489
#, no-wrap
msgid "The <c>mke2fs</c> command has a few interesting options as well:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:494
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Writing a file system to the disk is quite fast. If you want to check the \n"
"    device for bad blocks during the file system write, add a <c>-c</c> option.\n"
"    If you specify this option twice, a full read-write test is performed \n"
"    instead of a read-only test.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:500
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    To speed up lookups in large directories, you can enable directory indexing\n"
"    by adding <c>-O dir_index</c>. \n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:504
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Large file systems might free more space by adding <c>-O sparse_super</c>.\n"
"    This will decrease the percentage of blocks used as backups for the file\n"
"    metadata.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "The swap file system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:517
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although you can't 'use' the swap space directly, it does use a specific file\n"
"system to store the memory pages. To create a swap file system on the swap\n"
"partition, use <c>mkswap</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:522
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a swap file system on /dev/hda2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:523
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mkswap /dev/hda2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:527
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Unlike the other file system creation tools, <c>mkswap</c> hardly takes\n"
"additional options for tuning purposes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:534
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create the file systems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:538
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create the file systems on your partitions <e>now</e> and don't forget to create\n"
"the swap file system as well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:547
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting in the minimal environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:549
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting the partitions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:553
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The next step is to <e>mount</e> the file systems in the Linux file system\n"
"hierarchy so that you can use it. As we have said in the previous part, mounting\n"
"attaches the file system to the current hierarchy at a specified location.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:559
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On the Gentoo installation CD, a directory <path>/mnt/gentoo</path> is available\n"
"to mount your root file system in spe. Let us suppose that the file system is at\n"
"<path>/dev/hda3</path>, then the <c>mount</c> command would be:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:564
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting the root file system at /mnt/gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:565
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mount /dev/hda3 /mnt/gentoo</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:569
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You'll also need to mount the other file systems at the correct place. Because\n"
"your root file system doesn't contain any directories yet, you'll need to create\n"
"them. For instance, if you have a separate <path>/boot</path> (at\n"
"<path>/dev/hda1</path> and <path>/usr</path> (at <path>/dev/hda4</path>) file \n"
"system:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:576
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating mount points prior to mounting the file systems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:577
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mkdir /mnt/gentoo/boot /mnt/gentoo/usr</i>\n"
"# <i>mount /dev/hda4 /mnt/gentoo/usr</i>\n"
"# <i>mount /dev/hda1 /mnt/gentoo/boot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:583
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will also need to activate the swap partition. This is accomplished using\n"
"the <c>swapon</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:587
#, no-wrap
msgid "Activating the swap space"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Example for a swap file system at /dev/hda2)</comment>\n"
"# <i>swapon /dev/hda2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:595
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing the stage tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:599
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A Gentoo stage tarball contains a minimal Gentoo environment. If you are booted\n"
"from a Gentoo universal installation CD you might find the stage of your choice\n"
"on the CD (probably at <path>/mnt/cdrom/stages</path>). If not, you can download\n"
"one from one of our <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. They are stored\n"
"in the appropriate release directory under the name <path>stages/</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:608
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A <e>tarball</e> is an archive, usually compressed using Lempel-Ziv coding\n"
"(LZ77 - <c>gzip</c>) or Burrows-Wheeler compression with Huffman coding\n"
"(<c>bzip2</c>). Uncompressed, you will have a single file (a tar<sup>2</sup> \n"
"file) that contains all the files in the archive, nicely appended one after \n"
"another.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:616
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To download such a stage tarball, <e>first</e> go to <path>/mnt/gentoo</path>.\n"
"This is required so that, once you start downloading the file, it is stored on\n"
"the disk and not in memory (the Gentoo installation CD creates a virtual 'disk'\n"
"in memory so that you can use the CD without requiring any pre-installed Linux\n"
"system).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:623
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading a stage tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:624
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /mnt/gentoo</i>\n"
"# <i>lynx http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:629
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, extract the tarball to the <path>/mnt/gentoo</path> location. Use the\n"
"<c>tar</c> tool with <c>xjpf</c> as options and the tarball as argument:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:634
#, no-wrap
msgid "e<b>x</b>tract the files from the archive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:636
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    use <c>bunzip2</c> to decompress the archive (<b>j</b> due to shortage of\n"
"    available options :)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:639
#, no-wrap
msgid "<b>p</b>reserve the permissions that were stored in the tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:640
#, no-wrap
msgid "use the next <b>f</b>ile as the archive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:643
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting the stage tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:644
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>tar xjpf &lt;file&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:648
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your stage tarball is stored on the CD, just use the path to the file for\n"
"<path>&lt;file&gt;</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:653
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<sup>2</sup>: the name <e>tar</e> comes from Tape ARchive. The <c>tar</c> tool\n"
"was (and still is) commonly used for backing up files to tapes which only have\n"
"linear access (unlike digital media where you can quickly jump from one location\n"
"to another). Because of this limitation, all files are aligned after another\n"
"with a table of contents stored in the beginning of the tape. The <c>tar</c>\n"
"tool is still a very popular tool for creating archives.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting a Portage snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:668
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We need to extract another tarball, namely a <e>portage snapshot</e>. Portage is\n"
"the software management system Gentoo uses. The package information itself is\n"
"stored in what we call the <e>Portage tree</e>. A <e>portage snapshot</e>\n"
"is a Portage tree taken at a certain point in time. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:675
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On a universal installation CD, you might find such a snapshot at\n"
"<path>/mnt/gentoo/snapshot</path>, but you can always download a snapshot from\n"
"the Internet as well. Go to one of our <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri> and locate the\n"
"most recent portage snapshot in the <path>snapshots/</path> directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:682
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading a Portage tree snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:683
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>lynx http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:687
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We don't need any specific permission information from the snapshot, so the\n"
"<c>tar</c> command only requires <c>xjf</c> as options. However, the snapshot\n"
"<e>must</e> be extracted inside <path>/mnt/gentoo/usr</path>. We could do the\n"
"same as we did with the stage tarball and first go to\n"
"<path>/mnt/gentoo/usr</path> before we run the extraction command, but you can\n"
"also use <c>-C &lt;location&gt;</c> (with a capital C) to inform <c>tar</c> that\n"
"the <path>/mnt/gentoo/usr</path> location is the destination:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:696
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting a Portage tree snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:697
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>tar xjf &lt;snapshot&gt; -C /mnt/gentoo/usr</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:703
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing the minimal Gentoo environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:707
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you might have guessed already, we are trying to have \n"
"<path>/mnt/gentoo</path> contain a fully functional Linux environment. To finish\n"
"this off, we need to mount a specific <e>pseudo file system</e> called proc at\n"
"<path>/mnt/gentoo/proc</path>. This is not a file system stored on a disk, but\n"
"rather an interface to the Linux kernel showing kernel information as regular\n"
"files. This allows you to retrieve kernel (and system) information by just\n"
"reading files instead of requiring specific tools.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:716
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting the proc file system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:717
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mount -t proc none /mnt/gentoo/proc</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:721
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To be able to use the network you have defined (if applicable), you need to copy\n"
"over the <path>/etc/resolv.conf</path> file to the new Linux environment:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:725
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying over the name resolving information file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>cp /etc/resolv.conf /mnt/gentoo/etc</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:732
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root from CD to the new environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:736
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The final step now is to change the root of your file system from the one\n"
"provided by the CD to the one you just set up, namely <path>/mnt/gentoo</path>.\n"
"Using the <c>chroot</c> tool, your terminal session will not see anything\n"
"outside <path>/mnt/gentoo</path> unless you finish the <c>chroot</c> itself.\n"
"Because you need a shell to navigate, we run <path>/bin/bash</path> (the Bourn\n"
"Again SHell) right after changing the root:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:744
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root to /mnt/gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-install-storage.xml:745
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>chroot /mnt/gentoo /bin/bash</i>\n"
msgstr ""
